HEADWORD: Epicurize
<hw>Ep"i*cu*rize</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To
profess or tend towards the doctrines of Epicurus.</def>
<rj><au>Cudworth.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To feed or indulge like an epicure.</def>
<rj><au>Fuller.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Epicycle</ent>⟦br⟧
